📘 Part 2: Mapper Concept (MapStruct)
Definition: Mapper ek aisa tool hai jo ek object (Entity) ke data ko doosre object (DTO) mein transfer karta hai. Ye sensitive data (jaise password) ko client se chhupane mein madad karta hai.
1. Mapping Tools Comparison Table
Feature	Manual Mapping	MapStruct	ModelMapper
How it works?	Code khud likhna padta hai	Interface se code generate hota hai	Runtime par match hota hai
Performance	Best	Excellent (Fastest)	Average (Slow)
Error Check	Manual check	Compile-time check	Runtime check
2. Complete Code Example (Custom Mapping)
The Objects (Entity & DTO):
java
public class User { // Database Entity
    private String fullName; // Different name
    private String email;
    private String password; // Don't want to show
}

public class UserDTO { // API Object
    private String name; // Different name
    private String email;
}
Use code with caution.

The Mapper Interface:
java
@Mapper
public interface UserMapper {
    UserMapper INSTANCE = Mappers.getMapper(UserMapper.class);

    // Agar names alag hain toh aise batate hain:
    @Mapping(source = "fullName", target = "name") 
    @Mapping(target = "password", ignore = true) // Password ko ignore karein
    UserDTO toDTO(User user);
}
Use code with caution.

💡 Interview Important Points (Summary)
YAML Rule: Kabhi Tab use mat karo, hamesha 2 Spaces use karo. Colon : ke baad ek space zaroori hai.
Why MapStruct? Kyunki ye Compile-time par code likhta hai, isliye ye fast hai aur error pehle hi pakad leta hai.
Separation of Concerns: Mapper use karne se hamara Business Logic (Service) aur Database Layer alag-alag rehte hain.
